<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-123-232  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 123 232.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  March 20 1989 n409 p51(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Battle for board seats begins: MAI challenges Prime with its ownslate of candidates. (MAI basic four tries to gain control ofPrime Computer board)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lazar, Jerry; McGee, Marianne Kolbasuk.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MAI Basic Four Inc (MBF) is seeking to take over Prime ComputerInc by exercising proxy votes to replace the Prime board with MBFcandidates at Prime's annual shareholders meeting May 12, 1989.andO;The MBF candidates' platform is to sell Prime to MBF if a betteroffer is not presented within 30 days of the meeting.andP;  Prime'scandidates offer a platform of growth through expansion ofinstalled base and penetration of specialized markets.andP;  Prime'sentire seven-member board is up for re-election.andP;  MBF's$20-per-share tender offer for Prime was accepted by more thanhalf of Prime's shareholders, and these shareholders may well givetheir proxy to MBF.andP;  Prime's terms of incorporation provide asingle vote for each share of stock.andP;  Because of delays inexecuting the tender offer it is unlikely that MBF will be able tovote the stock it has purchased.andP;  The rival MBF slate is legalaccording to Prime terms of incorporation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Prime Computer Inc. (management)MAI Basic Four Inc. (investment activities).andO;Ticker:    PRM; MBF.andO;Topic:     TakeoversBoard of Directors.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Bennett LeBow. (portrait)Anthony Craig. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>